# Repo Core Conventions (pandas stand-in)

You are working on the Trailhead pandas stand-in under `examples/pandas-standin/`.

## PR and commit standards

- PR titles MUST use a prefix: `ENH:`, `BUG:`, `DOC:`, `TST:`, `BLD:`, `PERF:`, `TYP:`, or `CLN:`
- One logical change per PR
- Reference a GitHub issue when the change is non-trivial

## Layout and tests

- Source changes live under `examples/pandas-standin/pandas/core/`
- Mirror tests under `examples/pandas-standin/pandas/tests/core/`:
  - `pandas/core/ops/common.py` → `pandas/tests/core/ops/test_common.py`
- Every new public function needs happy-path, edge-case, and error-case tests

## Library-specific APIs

- Check `scripts/deprecated-apis.json` before using existing functions
- Do not use `legacy_normalize` — use `normalize_values`

## Workflow

- Run `make check` before pushing
- Use `/scaffold-first-contribution` for guided first PRs
- Use `/pre-push-quality-gate` before push
